---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '@/config/site';

const post = {
  title: 'Inside our 2023 move to Chilsworthy.',
  description:
    "The story of WCCP's 2023 move from Shebbear to Chilsworthy — 46 new jobs, a modern batching plant, and the Severn Trent biogas neighbour that powers a circular-economy footprint.",
  datePublished: '2026-03-01',
  dateModified: '2026-03-01',
  author: 'WCCP Engineering Team',
  url: `${site.url}/news/chilsworthy-yard-modernisation`,
};

const schemaData = {
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  datePublished: post.datePublished,
  dateModified: post.dateModified,
  author: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: post.author,
    url: `${site.url}/team`,
  },
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: site.name,
    logo: {
      '@type': 'ImageObject',
      url: `${site.url}/logo.png`,
    },
  },
  mainEntityOfPage: {
    '@type': 'WebPage',
    '@id': post.url,
  },
  image: `${site.url}/images/wccp-yard-aerial-chilsworthy-holsworthy.png`,
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Inside our 2023 move to Chilsworthy — 46 jobs, modern plant, circular-economy footprint"
  description="The story of WCCP's 2023 move from Shebbear to Chilsworthy — 46 new jobs, a modern batching plant, and the Severn Trent biogas neighbour that powers a circular-economy footprint."
  schema="Article"
  schemaData={schemaData}
>
  <section class="bg-navy text-white">
    <div class="container-wccp py-14 md:py-16">
      <nav class="text-sm text-white/90 mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/news" class="hover:text-yellow">News</a><span class="mx-2 text-cast">/</span>
        <span class="text-white/90">Chilsworthy yard</span>
      </nav>
      <p class="eyebrow text-yellow mb-4">Company news · 1 March 2026</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-display-xl text-white mb-6 max-w-4xl">
        Inside our 2023 move to Chilsworthy.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-white/85 text-lg max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
        46 jobs, modern plant, a new circular-economy footprint — and the Severn Trent biogas
        neighbour that helps make it work.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-sm text-white/90">
        <div>By <span class="text-white font-semibold">WCCP Engineering Team</span></div>
        <div>Published <time datetime="2026-03-01">1 March 2026</time></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="container-wccp py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">

      <!-- Direct-answer block -->
      <aside class="bg-bone-200 border-l-4 border-ember p-6 rounded-r mb-10">
        <p class="eyebrow text-cast mb-2">In one paragraph</p>
        <p class="text-navy text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium">
          In 2023 West Country Concrete Products relocated from Shebbear to a purpose-built
          eight-acre yard at Chilsworthy, near Holsworthy on the Devon / Cornwall border. The move
          created 46 jobs (over 90% filled within 15 miles), introduced a modern batching plant
          with electronically logged mixes, longer prestressing beds, doubled cement-silo capacity
          and a covered casting hall. The yard sits beside Severn Trent Green Power's Holsworthy
          biogas plant, recycles process water and concrete returns, and houses our first full-time
          concrete laboratory.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a href="/factory" class="btn-primary text-sm">Tour the factory</a>
          <a href="/contact?subject=yard-visit" class="btn-yellow text-sm">Book a yard visit</a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- Lead photo -->
      <figure class="mb-10 rounded-lg overflow-hidden bg-cast-100">
        <picture>
          <source srcset="/images/wccp-yard-aerial-chilsworthy-holsworthy.webp" type="image/webp" />
          <img
            src="/images/wccp-yard-aerial-chilsworthy-holsworthy.png"
            alt="Aerial view of the WCCP precast yard at Chilsworthy, Holsworthy — purpose-built in 2023"
            class="w-full h-auto block"
            loading="eager"
            decoding="async"
            width="1600"
            height="900"
          />
        </picture>
        <figcaption class="bg-navy/95 text-white text-sm px-4 py-3">
          The Chilsworthy yard from the air — eight acres, purpose-built and opened in 2023.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-navy mb-4">Why we moved.</h2>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        We had outgrown Shebbear. The old yard had served us well since the 1970s — three
        generations of concrete had gone out of those gates — but the moulds were getting bigger,
        the jobs were getting heavier, and the access roads were not keeping up. In 2023 we
        completed the move to a new site at Chilsworthy, just outside Holsworthy on the
        Devon / Cornwall border.
      </p>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The decision was years in the making. By 2020 we were turning down bespoke jobs we should
        have been quoting for, simply because we could not lay the moulds out. The new
        prestressed range needed a 60-metre casting bed; the old yard could give us 38 on a good
        day. HGV access was tight enough that loading a 14m panel meant moving four other lorries
        first. The move was not a lifestyle choice — it was the only way to keep growing without
        sending customers to a competitor.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-navy mb-4">46 jobs.</h2>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The move created 46 roles — drivers, batchers, fitters, design engineers, yard hands and
        admin staff. Over 90% of those jobs are filled by people living within 15 miles of the
        yard. North Devon is not flush with manufacturing employment; we are proud the move kept
        skilled jobs in the area and brought new ones with it. Today the team is 46 strong and
        we are still hiring on the production side. Anyone interested in joining us can read the
        current <a href="/careers" class="text-ember underline">vacancies on the careers page</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-navy mb-4">The new plant.</h2>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        A modern batching plant, longer casting beds, larger overhead cranes — and the room to
        run a proper factory production control system. Every batch is now logged
        electronically, every cube test traceable to the load. <a href="/standards-explained#bs-en-13369" class="text-ember underline">BS EN 13369</a>
        compliance is easier when the kit is built for it.
      </p>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        We doubled cement silo capacity, brought in a new computer-controlled mixer that holds
        water content to a tenth of a percent, and built a covered casting hall so winter pours
        no longer wait on the weather. A dedicated bespoke bay sits alongside the standard
        production line, which means one-off jobs no longer queue behind the day's cubicle run.
        For the customer the practical wins are shorter lead times, a longer working day at the
        yard, and capacity for the heavier prestressed sections we could not previously cast.
      </p>

      <!-- Inline photo placeholder: pour / casting (pending real WCCP yard photography) -->
      <figure class="my-10 rounded-lg overflow-hidden bg-cast-100">
        <div class="aspect-[16/9] flex items-center justify-center border-2 border-dashed border-cast-300 p-8 text-center">
          <div>
            <p class="text-cast-600 text-sm font-mono">📷 Photo needed</p>
            <p class="text-cast text-xs mt-2">Concrete being poured into a precast mould on the new line at Chilsworthy</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figcaption class="bg-navy/95 text-white text-sm px-4 py-3">
          Pouring on the new line — every batch is logged electronically and tied back to a cube test.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-navy mb-4">The biogas neighbour.</h2>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Across the road sits the Holsworthy Biogas Plant — operated by Severn Trent Green Power
        (a FTSE-100 utility). It takes farm slurry from across North Devon and turns it into
        renewable electricity. We supply
        <a href="/products/ad-plant-components" class="text-ember underline">precast components for AD plants</a>
        of exactly that kind. Living next door to one is a useful reminder of who our
        engineering serves.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-navy mb-4">Circular economy.</h2>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The new yard re-uses concrete returns and aggregate fines back into non-structural pours.
        Process water is captured and recycled. Mould oils are bio-based where the spec allows.
        These are small things by themselves; together they shift the footprint of every panel
        we cast.
      </p>

      <!-- Inline photo placeholder: loading / lorry (pending real WCCP yard photography) -->
      <figure class="my-10 rounded-lg overflow-hidden bg-cast-100">
        <div class="aspect-[16/9] flex items-center justify-center border-2 border-dashed border-cast-300 p-8 text-center">
          <div>
            <p class="text-cast-600 text-sm font-mono">📷 Photo needed</p>
            <p class="text-cast text-xs mt-2">HIAB lorry being loaded with precast panels at the Chilsworthy yard hardstanding</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figcaption class="bg-navy/95 text-white text-sm px-4 py-3">
          Loading out — proper hardstanding for HGVs was one of the reasons we moved.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-navy mb-4">A good neighbour.</h2>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Moving a working concrete yard into a rural village is a real change for the community.
        We take being a good neighbour seriously — yard hours, dust suppression, traffic routing
        and a direct line for residents. Read the full
        <a href="/community" class="text-ember underline">community commitments</a> page.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/about" class="btn-primary">Our story</a>
        <a href="/factory" class="btn-yellow">The factory</a>
        <a href="/contact?subject=yard-visit" class="btn-secondary">Book a yard visit</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <section class="bg-bone-200 py-12">
    <div class="container-wccp">
      <a href="/news" class="text-ember font-bold">← Back to news</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
